description: With the forces of the undead converging on the Nation's capital from outside the Beltway, the army of zombies created within explodes with cannibalistic fury and the thinly-stretched forces of the National Guard are nearly powerless to curb the tide of murder sweeping through Washington D.C. As the living dead claw at the very gates of the White House, desperate measures give way to a flight for survival. No one is safe, no one is immune and there is nowhere to run as the Apocalypse approaches, ushered in by the clawing hands of blood-thirsty fiends intent of devouring every living human in their path.
name: 5 (of 5)

description: Conan goes against his Cimmerian instincts and sides with Pelias the wizard, who can help the barbarian exact revenge on those who took his crown! Conan races to Aquilonia to regain his throne!
name: The Halls Of Hell, Part 4 of 4

description: En route for the World Cup final in 1966, the Doctor, Amy, and Rory find themselves in London a thousand years in the past! And Vikings and Saxons are fighting over who owns the land-and Amy! Can Rory win his new wife back... in a penalty shootout?
name: They Think It's All Over

description: Conan has been in trouble before, but never like this! It may just be the end of the line for everyone's favorite barbarian! Join Conan as he braves Ophir's golden court as he tries to save Olivia from the power of the mystic ring known as the Star of Khorala. Conan will need both luck and skill if he's to escape the axe of Ophir's savage executioner!
name: [Untitled]

description:
With the hardcover collection of LEGION LOST coming in June, DC Comics collects the tale that led into that space-spanning epic: LEGION OF THE DAMNED, originally published in LEGIONNAIRES #79-80 and LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES #122-123.

Featuring spectacular art by Olivier Coipel, the story begins as Cosmic Boy, Brainiac 5 and other heroes return to Earth, only to find it dominated by the alien race known as the Blight. How can the team stop these alien invaders when they're being picked off one by one?
name: Legion of The Damned

description: Anita Blake is back in the second volume of Marvel's comic adaptation of Laurell K. Hamilton's bestselling series of novels! What would you do for a million dollars? description:
Overview

This was the 24th adventure of Tintin that was unfinished at the time of Herge's death on 3rd March 1983. Herge's wife originally gave permission for this story to be finished by other artists but then took it back when she deicided he would not want Tintin's adventures to be finished by anyone else. A version was released using all the unfinished art and plot notes by Herge and is considered too be the official end to the series.
name: Tintin and Alph-Art

description:
Overview

Tintin and the Lake of Sharks in its original series was known as "Tintin et le Lac aux Requins". It is a Tintin animated film directed by Raymond Leblanc in 1972. It was not written by Hergé but by the Belgian comics creator Greg (Michel Regnier), a friend of Hergé. It was later adapted into this comic book with still images from the film.
name: Tintin and the Lake of Sharks

The 1980s adventures of the Justice League continue in this new volume starring Batman, Blue Beetle, Booster Gold and many other heroes. Two branches of the Justice League – Justice League American and Justice League International – team up in this volume to face the threat of what appears to be vampires in the Balkans.

Collects Justice League America #31-35 and Justice League Europe #7-11. Includes The Teasdale Imperative crossover.
